onse Time Degradation**\n   - Pod `recommendationservice-2` experienced an increase in `rrt_max` from `22437.0` to `2450581.5` and `rrt` from `4162.73` to `307492.07`. This is a clear indicator of service degradation affecting response times.\n\n3. **Frontend Service Response Time Increase**\n   - Pods `frontend-0`, `frontend-1`, `frontend-2` exhibited increased `rrt_max` and `rrt` with median change ratios reaching up to `1.7581`.\n\n4. **Redis Cart Service RRT Max Decrease**\n   - Pod `redis-cart-0` saw a decrease in `rrt_max` from `10749.0` to `8439.0` indicating a reduction in maximum request response time, which may or may not correlate with faults but it's worth noting.\n\n5. **Node CPU and Memory Usage**\n   - Node `aiops-k8s-01` exhibited a decrease in `node_cpu_usage_rate` from `35.21` to `22.82`, and `node_memory_usage_rate` decreased from `46.46` to `26.58`. Despite reductions, these shifts might impact the deployment due to redistribution or system adjustments.\n\n### Hypotheses:\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"NEUTRAL\",\n  \"detected_metric_keys\": [\n    \"pod_cpu_usage\", \n    \"rrt_max\", \n    \"node_memory_usage_rate\"\n  ],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"Recommendation Service\",\n      \"reason\": \"High CPU usage and increased response times (`pod_cpu_usage`, `rrt_max`) indicating resource strain or inefficient processing\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Pods `recommendationservice-0`, `recommendationservice-1`, `recommendationservice-2` showed significant CPU usage increase resulting in response delays.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"Frontend Service\",\n      \"reason\": \"Response time degradation (`rrt_max`, `rrt`) highlighting potential network latency or downstream service impact\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Increased metrics in `frontend-0`, `frontend-1`, `frontend-2` with response times extending into fault period.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"Node Configurations\",\n      \"reason\": \"Resource allocation imbalance (`node_cpu_usage_rate`, `node_memory_usage_rate`) possibly affecting load distributions or service efficiency\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Node `aiops-k8s-01` displayed significant reductions in resource utilization metrics.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\nThis findings suggest a mix of pod-level resource bottlenecks coinciding with node-level adjustments, warranting further inspection into service processing efficiency and potential node redistribution or configuration anomalies."}
